spans.text: Those painted pinions light and gay
thy once loved shrine See what gay flowers thy bust entwine
didst thou promise thou wouldst be , Next to fond Fancy , kind to me
my sight a length of way
leave my sight a length of way
a landscape sweet and fair That mingled with the softest air , And painted Days of other hue , And Evenings spangled over with dew , And Hours that , laughing as they trodden
dost thou fly me ? — Goddess , stay !
! she now arrests my breath , And almost threatens instant death ; A lifeless calm she now demands , And ties my weak unmoving hands
The softest way to sweetest sound
melting with the plaintive air Seemed a weak sort of echo there
that oft has found The softest way to sweetest sound , And thrilling yet along the line Would aid this falling note of mine , Then melting with the plaintive air Seemed a weak sort of echo there
it is not given in vain
in a world of woes I'm tossed
